<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Admin" content-collection-id="NYCadmin" source-infobase-title="New York City Administrative Code" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\NYCadmin.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCadmin_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCadmin_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-685" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-7197" number="9643" version="803">
			<HEADING>Chapter 10: Prevention of Interference with Reproductive Health Services</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2165" name="T10C010"/>Chapter 10: Prevention of Interference with Reproductive Health Services</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-7198" number="9644" version="3">
				<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
					<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> This chapter was formerly designated as Chapter 8 of <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="T08" destination-id="0-0-0-2039">Title 8</LINK>.</PARA>
			</RECORD>
		</LEVEL>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-688" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Appendix" style-name-escaped="Appendix" style-id="0-0-0-691" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-694" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Article" style-name-escaped="Article" style-id="0-0-0-697" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle" style-name-escaped="Subarticle" style-id="0-0-0-700" level-depth="7" toc-section="false">
							<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle - Part" style-name-escaped="Subarticle---Part" style-id="0-0-0-29474" level-depth="8" toc-section="false">
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-7199" number="9645" version="3">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1001 Short title. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2631" name="10-1001"/>§ 10-1001 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Short title. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7200" number="9646" version="3">
											<PARA>This chapter shall be known and may be cited as the &quot;access to reproductive health care facilities law&quot;. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7201" number="9647" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7202" number="9648" version="1403">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2009/024" destination-id="0-0-0-24924">L.L. 2009/024</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-083]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-206225" number="9649" version="1403">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1002 Definitions. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2633" name="10-1002"/>§ 10-1002 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7203" number="9650" version="3">
											<PARA>As used in this chapter, the following terms have the following meanings:</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7204" number="9651" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Person.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;person&quot; means an individual, corporation, not-for-profit organization, partnership, association, group or any other entity. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7205" number="9652" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Premises of a reproductive health care facility.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;premises of a reproductive health care facility&quot; means the driveway, entrance, entryway, or exit of a reproductive health care facility and the building in which such facility is located and any parking lot in which the facility has an ownership or leasehold interest. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7206" number="9653" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Reproductive health care facility.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;reproductive health care facility&quot; means any building, structure or place, or any portion thereof, at which licensed, certified or otherwise legally authorized persons provide health care services or health care counseling relating to the human reproductive system. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7207" number="9654" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7208" number="9655" version="1403">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2009/024" destination-id="0-0-0-24924">L.L. 2009/024</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-083]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-206226" number="9656" version="1403">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1003 Prohibition of activities to prevent access to reproductive health care facilities. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2635" name="10-1003"/>§ 10-1003 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Prohibition of activities to prevent access to reproductive health care facilities. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7209" number="9657" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Unlawful conduct.</CHARFORMAT> It is unlawful for any person: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7210" number="9658" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To knowingly physically obstruct or block another person from entering into or exiting from the premises of a reproductive health care facility by physically striking, shoving, restraining, grabbing, or otherwise subjecting a person to unwanted physical contact, or attempting to do the same; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7211" number="9659" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To knowingly obstruct or block the premises of a reproductive health care facility, so as to impede access to or from the facility, or to attempt to do the same; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7212" number="9660" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To follow and harass another person within 15 feet of the premises of a reproductive health care facility; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7213" number="9661" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>4.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To engage in a course of conduct or repeatedly commit acts within 15 feet of the premises of a reproductive health care facility when such behavior places another person in reasonable fear of physical harm, or to attempt to do the same; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7214" number="9662" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>5.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To physically damage a reproductive health care facility so as to interfere with its operation, or to attempt to do the same; or <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7215" number="9663" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>6.<TAB tab-count="1"/>To knowingly interfere with the operation of a reproductive health care facility, or to attempt to do the same, by activities that include, but are not limited to, interfering with, or attempting to interfere with (i) medical procedures being performed at such facility or (ii) the delivery of goods to such facility. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7216" number="9664" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Violations.</CHARFORMAT> Any person who violates any provision of subdivision a of this section is guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine not to exceed $1,000 or imprisonment not to exceed six months, or both, for a first conviction under this section. For a second and each subsequent conviction under this section, the penalty shall be a fine not to exceed $5,000 or imprisonment not to exceed one year, or both. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7217" number="9665" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7218" number="9666" version="1403">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2009/024" destination-id="0-0-0-24924">L.L. 2009/024</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-083]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-206227" number="9667" version="1403">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1004 Civil cause of action. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2637" name="10-1004"/>§ 10-1004 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Civil cause of action. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7219" number="9668" version="3">
											<PARA>Where there has been a violation of subdivision a of section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="10-803" destination-id="0-0-0-2623">10-1003</LINK>, any person whose ability to access a reproductive health care facility has been interfered with, and any owner or operator of a reproductive health care facility or owner of a building in which such a facility is located, may bring a civil action in any court of competent jurisdiction for any or all of the following relief: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7220" number="9669" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Injunctive relief; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7221" number="9670" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Treble the amount of actual damages suffered as a result of such violation, including, where applicable, damages for pain and suffering and emotional distress, or damages in the amount of $5,000, whichever is greater; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7222" number="9671" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>c.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Attorney&apos;s fees and costs. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7223" number="9672" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7224" number="9673" version="1403">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2009/024" destination-id="0-0-0-24924">L.L. 2009/024</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-083]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-206228" number="9674" version="1403">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1005 Civil action by city to enjoin interference with access to reproductive health care facilities. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2639" name="10-1005"/>§ 10-1005 Civil action by city to enjoin interference with access to reproductive health care facilities<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7225" number="9675" version="3">
											<PARA>The corporation counsel may bring a civil action on behalf of the city in any court of competent jurisdiction for injunctive and other appropriate equitable relief in order to prevent or cure a violation of subdivision a of section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="10-803" destination-id="0-0-0-2623">10-1003</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7226" number="9676" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7227" number="9677" version="1403">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2009/024" destination-id="0-0-0-24924">L.L. 2009/024</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-083]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-206229" number="9678" version="1403">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1006 Joint and several liability. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2641" name="10-1006"/>§ 10-1006 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Joint and several liability. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7228" number="9679" version="3">
											<PARA>If it is found, in any action brought pursuant to the provisions of this chapter, that two or more of the named defendants acted in concert pursuant to a common plan or design to violate any provision of subdivision a of section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="10-1003" destination-id="0-0-0-2635">10-1003</LINK>, such defendants shall be held jointly and severally liable for any fines or penalties imposed or any damages awarded.</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7229" number="9680" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-7230" number="9681" version="3">
										<HEADING>§ 10-1007 Construction. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2643" name="10-1007"/>§ 10-1007 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Construction. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7231" number="9682" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>This chapter does not limit the right of any person or entity to seek other available criminal penalties or civil remedies. The penalties and remedies provided under this chapter are cumulative and are not exclusive. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7232" number="9683" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>This chapter does not prohibit expression protected by the first amendment of the constitution of the United States or section 8 of article 1 of the constitution of the state of New York. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-7233" number="9684" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>c.<TAB tab-count="1"/>This chapter does not limit the lawful exercise of any authority vested in the owner or operator of a reproductive health care facility, the owner of the premises in which such a facility is located, or a law enforcement officer of the city, the state of New York or the United States acting within the scope of such person&apos;s official duties. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
